{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"bluff-vault-rant","description":"## Summary\n`rebar reconcile --mode reconcile-check` (the read-only online drift diagnostic in `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/__main__.py`) loads local tickets by reading `<entry>/ticket.json` from each `.tickets-tracker/<id>/` directory. The event-sourced store NEVER writes `ticket.json` — a ticket dir contains event-log files (`*-CREATE.json`, `*-COMMENT.json`, …) plus a compiled `.cache.json` whose `state` key holds the ticket. So `local_tickets` is always empty, and every binding is classified 'bound but missing locally or in Jira'.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. On a populated event-sourced store with N confirmed bindings, run `rebar reconcile --mode reconcile-check`.\n2. Observe `bridge_state/reconcile-check.json`.\n\nExpected: bindings whose local ticket AND Jira issue both exist are counted checked/in_sync.\nActual: `checked: 0`, `in_sync: 0`, `orphaned_bindings` = all N (e.g. 627/627), regardless of true state. Confirmed live 2026-07-03 against production Jira REB (~628 issues, 627 bindings): acli fetch works (30 active issues returned), yet reconcile-check reported all 627 orphaned.\n\n## Root Cause\n`__main__.py` reconcile-check branch: `meta_path = entry / \"ticket.json\"` — a file the event-sourced store does not produce. `ticket.json` is referenced ONLY here; no other reconciler code reads it. The compiled ticket is `.cache.json['state']` (fields keyed `ticket_id`, `status`, `ticket_type`, `tags`, …), or can be obtained by replaying the event log.\n\n## Impact\nThe read-only drift diagnostic is unusable — it always reports 100% orphaned drift (false positive). It does NOT affect the live-acting pass (run_pass/the differs load local state through a different, correct path), so no bad mutations result; but any operator relying on reconcile-check for a go/no-go read gets a totally misleading census.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] reconcile-check's local loader reads the compiled ticket from `.cache.json['state']` (or replays the event log) instead of the nonexistent `ticket.json`, keying on `ticket_id`/`status`.\n- [ ] On a store where a binding's local ticket and Jira issue both exist, reconcile-check counts it checked/in_sync (not orphaned); a RED unit test in `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/` reproduces the all-orphaned bug and passes after the fix.\n- [ ] No regression to the live-acting pass (that path is unaffected).\n- [ ] Landed on main via Gerrit (LLM-Review + Verified).","id":"ad39-5017-802d-4941","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"reconcile-check reads nonexistent per-ticket ticket.json -> falsely reports ALL bindings orphaned"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783139710156807001,"uuid":"c842bd1a-7348-48b1-b4ab-7f9540828176"}